com.gl.vn.me.ko.pies.base.main

Class GuiceLocator

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.gl.vn.me.ko.pies.base.main.GuiceLocator

  • public final class GuiceLocator
extends Object
    Allows to conveniently locate published instances of GuiceModule.

    GuiceModule respects ApplicationConfig.getStage() when creates instances of Injector.

      • getModules

        public static final Set<GuiceModule> getModules(String... names)
                                         throws GuiceModuleNotFoundException
        Returns published instances of GuiceModule according to the requested names. Multiple invocations of the method with the same modules requested will result to the same objects returned, i.e. each GuiceModule is instantiated only once.

        It's important that instances of GuiceModule are requested by name and not by class, because otherwise if there are API and implementation JAR's, GuiceModule can only be published by code in implementation JAR and requesting it by class would create a compile-time dependency on the implementation JAR.

        Parameters:
        names - Names of the required modules.
        Returns:
        Requested modules.
        Throws:
        GuiceModuleNotFoundException - If lookup of at least one requested GuiceModule is failed.
